HEADWORD: Corky
<hw>Cork"y</hw> <pr>(-⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Consisting of, or like, cork; dry shriveled up.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Bind fast hiss <qex>corky</qex> arms.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tasting of cork.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corm</ent>⟦br⟧
